title: For Sale/Trade:  Everything you need to get you going for precision reloading .308, .223/5.56, & 9mm
postcontent:
Everything you need to get you going for precision reloading .308, .223/5.56, & 9mm.
I purchased all equipment that was highly rated and the best in class for each caliber. Unfortunately I just don’t go to the range at all which completely defeated the purpose of getting into reloading. I will break everything down into content sections to be as thorough as possible. 
Contents:
1)	Hornady Lock-N-Load Classic Kit [$383.06] - This is everything that will get you started for the reloading process. Below is a list of the included items.
a-	Lock-N-Load Classic Single-Stage Press w/ piece of priming large and small primers. (This is separate from the actual hand-held primer that is included as well. It is just another way I found that I like to prime cases.) Also includes a little primer catcher that attaches to the inside of the press to catch primers as you deprime your cases.
b-	Lock-N-Load Powder measure - This is actually brand new and never used. Never got around to needing it since I didn’t load but a couple hundred cases of different calibers.
c-	Electronic Scale – Reviews aren’t great but I didn’t have any issues with this. Took excellent care of it and found that if you do the “CAL” and the “tear” after every 10-15 cases is it fairly precise, even for .308 Precision long range loading.
d-	9th Edition (and most recent) Hornady Reloading Manual
e-	Three Lock-N-Load Die Bushings – I actually purchased a LOT more of these for every single one of my dies. These quick change bushings are amazing and this is what makes the Hornady Press one of the best on the market. With a couple seconds you are able to change out a die while keeping the same settings from die to die.
f-	Hand-Held Priming Tool.
g-	Universal Reloading Block – I purchased an extra one of these so I could finish a step and move the case to the other block. This keeps you organized and efficient/proficient.
h-	Chamfering/Deburring Tool.
i-	Primer Turning Plate – This helps you put primers and shake them to turn them right side up to use the hand-held primer tool.
j-	Powder Funnel – Used when hand powder charging a case. Works great and I haven’t had any issues with powder sticking to the inside due to static electricity.
k-	Powder Trickler – Great when you are trying to get a precise load. It will trickle out a couple grains of powder very slowly.

2)	Reloading Die Sets:
a-	9mm – Lyman 9mm Lugar Carbide 4-Die Set. [$67.99] – VERY highly rated. I like this because unlike most kits this comes with a separate taper crimp die. Perfect set and worked amazing for the few 9mm cases that I reloaded. Worked flawless for an FNX-9, XD-9, Glock 23 w/ conversion 9mm barrel.
b-	.223/5.56 – RCBS Small Base Die Set [$39.99] w/ the Lee Precision .223/5.56 Factory Crimp Die [$12.99] – The small base kit is perfect for reloading for an AR-15 semi-auto platform or a .223/5.56 bolt action rifle. This is one of the most used/highest rated sets on the market. The Lee FCD is one of the only tools that every reloader typically uses for crimping their AR-15 rounds to be used in a magazine. 
c-	.308 - Forster Full Length Sizer & Bench Rest Seater Die Set [$82.99] – This is the highest rated die set for high precision .308 reloading on the market (just check out MidwayUSA ratings). This usually sells out at most online stores. Forster is well known for their precision parts in the reloading circles. A large portion of competition and long range shooters use these dies exclusively.

3)	Extra Reloading Accessories:
a-	Lyman Case Prep Xpress 110v System [$129.99] – Fully automatic case prepping made easy! Includes accessories to chamfer/deburr/ream military 308 & 5.56 primed brass pockets/brush/clean primer pockets. This is for large and small primer pocket cases. One of the best investments if you plan on doing a lot of reloading. I also recent had Lyman send me another chamfer which is unused for chamfering case mouths. 
b-	Lee Decapping Die [$11.89] – Used to decap/deprime once fired brass (any size). I like using this before cleaning brass. A lot of people use the deprimer in the sizing die but cleaning your brass without the primer in it is optimal.
c-	.30 CAL RCBS Flash Hole Deburring Tool with Pilot Case Stop [$12.49]
d-	.22 CAL RCBS Flash Hole Deburring Tool with Pilot Case Stop [$12.49]
e-	Lee Case Trimmer [$20.00] – Includes the pilot/trimmer/shell holder for a .308 & the pilot/trimmer/shell holder for .223/5.56.
f-	Hornady Shell Holders [In Total Approx. $13.00] - #1/8/16 – This will cover most the major calibers. Will work for the 9mm Lugar/.308 WIN/.223-5.56 REM.
g-	Hornady Universal Reloading Tray [$8.99] – This is extra one that I purchased. It is the same as the one that comes with the Reloading Kit. Better to have multiples of these. This tray is highly rated and very easy to use for multiple calibers.
h-	EGW 4-Hole Chamber Checker Max Cartridge Gage (9mm Luger, 38 Super, 40 S&W, 45 ACP) [$19.99] – I used this to check my cases and ammo after I was done reloading. This helps you determine if your ammo will fit in the tightest chambers.
i-	L.E. Wilson Case Length Headspace Gage .223-5.56 Remington [$26.99] – Highest rated chamber checker for your reloaded rounds. This is a must if you are reloading for an AR-15. Just slide each loaded round in this real quick and it’ll show you if it’s too short/long/tight/loose and etc. This is a must!
j-	iGaging ABSOLUTE ORIGIN 0-6" Digital Electronic Caliper [$39.95] – Watched a LOT of videos online and read a lot of reviews for Digital Calipers. This is one of the most affordable but one of the most reliable. The repeatability and accuracy is amazing. This is needed for case trimming/bullet seating if not for a lot of other reloading aspects. Helps in setting up dies as well.
k-	Hornady Quick Change Lock-N-Load Die Bushings [$50.00] - x13
l-	x4 MTM 9mm 100 round Ammo Cases [$16.00] – Green See-through tops with black bottoms. Purchased these for my 9mm reloads. Nice cases.


Condition:
Everything is in pristine condition. Unlike a lot of people who just get into reloading for the heck of it and don’t take care of their stuff, I do. The first thing I did when I purchased everything is degrease EVERYTHING including the press, the dies, and accessories. Then lubed/cleaned them very well with Hornady One Shot Dry Lube. This stuff is amazing and I highly suggest you use this. I broke down every piece on the dies and wiped them down and lubed them with the Hornady One Shot Dry Lube. This is highly recommended with new dies. I kept everything highly organized. I went to the craft section if Walmart and purchased heavy duty plastic containers to organize all my dies. I made sure everything fit precisely in it and everything made sense. After cleaning every die I screwed on a Lock-N-Load Die Bushing to make sure every die had a quick change bushing. These bushings are what make Hornady’s reloading press so extremely popular and precise. Unless you get the conversion kit for other presses this is the only one that lets change out dies without having to readjust them every time. This made reloading for 9mm so easy. I would seat about 15-20 at a time then switch to crimping them. Then immediately switch back. The seater die stayed right at 1.100” when I twisted it back into place. Just look up the YouTube Videos or read reviews.

Other Thoughts:
	I put a lot of thought into this entire set for a significant amount of time. I’ve been into reloading for some time. Unfornately, I am no long able to go to the range as much as I used to go. This defeats the purpose of reloading to me. I handpicked every item after a lot of consideration. I also spent hours upon hours on forums like Sniperhide, THR, AR15.com, and several other reloading forums to find the best items. I spent a good chuck of money but I made sure I only had to buy once for 9mm/.308/.223-5.56 reloading. I’ve known a LOT of people who upgrade and upgrade to just get to the items that I considered and they ended up spending 3 times as much because they kept changing their mind. Check out the reviews on OpticPlanet, Amazon, Cabellas, MidwayUSA, Brownells & other places for each item that I am offering. I guarantee you that every one of them is 4.5 stars or higher. I made sure EVERYTHING I purchased was thoroughly reviewed and highly rated.
	I have highly detailed excel sheets that I put together for each and every round/component that was purchased or loaded. Very easy to use if I email them to you. The .308 rounds are ready to go to find your Optimal Charge Weight for high precision shooting (that is why 44 have been loaded). I'm a scientist at heart, so I usually work like I am at my lab, efficient, organized and thorough.
